"title": "7266: tribes of Israel",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7266",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The divisions of Israel on lines of kinship, according to descent from the twelve sons of Jacob. These divisions were most pronounced in the period before Saul became king of Israel but were maintained throughout Israel's history.</p>\n<h2>Origin of the tribes of Israel</h2>\n<h3>Twelve sons of Jacob</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:22-Gen35:26\">GEN 35:22–35:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen29:31-Gen29:35\">GEN 29:31–29:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:3-Gen30:13\">GEN 30:3–30:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen30:17-Gen30:24\">GEN 30:17–30:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:16-Gen35:18\">GEN 35:16–35:18</a></p>\n<h3>Increased in number while living in Egypt</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:5-Gen46:27\">GEN 46:5–46:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod1:1-Exod1:7\">EXO 1:1–1:7</a></p>\n<h2>Blessings on the tribes of Israel</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:1-Gen49:28\">GEN 49:1–49:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:1-Deut33:29\">DEU 33:1–33:29</a></p>\n<h2>Association of the twelve apostles with the tribes of Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:28\">MAT 19:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:1-Matt10:4\">MAT 10:1–10:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:13-Mark3:19\">MRK 3:13–3:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:12-Luke6:16\">LUK 6:12–6:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:28-Luke22:30\">LUK 22:28–22:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:12-Acts1:26\">ACT 1:12–1:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:12-Rev21:14\">REV 21:12–21:14</a></p>\n<h2>Other NT references to the tribes of Israel</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:1\">JAS 1:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:6-Acts26:7\">ACT 26:6–26:7</a></p>\n<h2>The tribes of Israel in end-time prophecy</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:1-Rev7:8\">REV 7:1–7:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek47:13-Ezek47:14\">EZK 47:13–47:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek48:1-Ezek48:35\">EZK 48:1–48:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev21:9-Rev21:14\">REV 21:9–21:14</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Asher</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Asher</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:17\">GEN 46:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:44-Num26:47\">NUM 26:44–26:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr7:30-1Chr7:40\">1CH 7:30–7:40</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Asher</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:40-Num1:41\">NUM 1:40–1:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:25-Num10:28\">NUM 10:25–10:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:12-Deut27:13\">DEU 27:12–27:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:24-Josh19:31\">JOS 19:24–19:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:22-Judg7:23\">JDG 7:22–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:6-2Chr30:11\">2CH 30:6–30:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:36-Luke2:38\">LUK 2:36–2:38</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Benjamin</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Benjamin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:21\">GEN 46:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:38-Num26:41\">NUM 26:38–26:41</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr7:6-1Chr7:12\">1CH 7:6–7:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr8:1-1Chr8:40\">1CH 8:1–8:40</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr9:1-1Chr9:9\">1CH 9:1–9:9</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Benjamin</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:36-Num1:37\">NUM 1:36–1:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:18-Num2:23\">NUM 2:18–2:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:12\">DEU 27:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:11-Josh18:28\">JOS 18:11–18:28</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:1-1Chr12:2\">1CH 12:1–12:2</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:1-Judg21:23\">JDG 19:1–21:23</a> <em>the war against Benjamin</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:21-1Kgs12:24\">1KI 12:21–12:24</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:1-2Chr11:4\">2CH 11:1–11:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:5-2Chr11:12\">2CH 11:5–11:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra1:5\">EZR 1:5</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Dan</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Dan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:42-Num26:43\">NUM 26:42–26:43</a></strong></p>\n<h3>The history of Dan</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:38-Num1:39\">NUM 1:38–1:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:25\">NUM 2:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:25\">NUM 10:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:12-Deut27:13\">DEU 27:12–27:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:40-Josh19:47\">JOS 19:40–19:47</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:1-Judg18:31\">JDG 18:1–18:31</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Ephraim</h2>\n<h3>The tribe of Ephraim was descended from Joseph's younger son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:4\">JOS 14:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:1-Gen48:20\">GEN 48:1–48:20</a></p>\n<h3>The genealogy of Ephraim</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:35-Num26:37\">NUM 26:35–26:37</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr7:20-1Chr7:29\">1CH 7:20–7:29</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Ephraim</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:32-Num1:33\">NUM 1:32–1:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:18\">NUM 2:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh16:1-Josh16:10\">JOS 16:1–16:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh17:14-Josh17:18\">JOS 17:14–17:18</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:29\">JDG 1:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:22-Judg8:3\">JDG 7:22–8:3</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg12:1-Judg12:6\">JDG 12:1–12:6</a> <em>the war against Ephraim</em></p>\n<h3>Later prophecies against Ephraim</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa7:2-Isa7:9\">ISA 7:2–7:9</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Gad</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Gad</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:16\">GEN 46:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:15-Num26:18\">NUM 26:15–26:18</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Gad</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:24-Num1:25\">NUM 1:24–1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:10-Num2:14\">NUM 2:10–2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:28-Num32:36\">NUM 32:28–32:36</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:12-Deut3:17\">DEU 3:12–3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:7-Deut29:8\">DEU 29:7–29:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:24-Josh13:28\">JOS 13:24–13:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:12-Josh1:18\">JOS 1:12–1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:10-Josh4:13\">JOS 4:10–4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:1-Josh22:34\">JOS 22:1–22:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:18-1Chr5:22\">1CH 5:18–5:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:25-1Chr5:26\">1CH 5:25–5:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:37\">1CH 12:37</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Issachar</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Issachar</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:13\">GEN 46:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:23-Num26:25\">NUM 26:23–26:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr7:1-1Chr7:5\">1CH 7:1–7:5</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Issachar</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:28-Num1:29\">NUM 1:28–1:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:3-Num2:6\">NUM 2:3–2:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:12\">DEU 27:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:17-Josh19:23\">JOS 19:17–19:23</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg10:1\">JDG 10:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:38-1Chr12:40\">1CH 12:38–12:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:10-2Chr30:20\">2CH 30:10–30:20</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Judah</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Judah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:19-Num26:22\">NUM 26:19–26:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:8-Gen46:12\">GEN 46:8–46:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr2:1-1Chr4:23\">1CH 2:1–4:23</a></p>\n<h3>The tribe of Judah in the wilderness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:26-Num1:27\">NUM 1:26–1:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:3-Num2:4\">NUM 2:3–2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:1-Num13:6\">NUM 13:1–13:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:16-Num34:19\">NUM 34:16–34:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:11-Deut27:12\">DEU 27:11–27:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:7\">DEU 33:7</a></p>\n<h3>Judah was prominent among the tribes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen49:8-Gen49:12\">GEN 49:8–49:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:1-Num2:9\">NUM 2:1–2:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num7:10-Num7:17\">NUM 7:10–7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num10:11-Num10:14\">NUM 10:11–10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:1-Judg1:20\">JDG 1:1–1:20</a></p>\n<h3>The territory of the tribe of Judah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh18:5\">JOS 18:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:21\">JOS 11:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh15:1-Josh15:63\">JOS 15:1–15:63</a> <em>the extent of the allotment for Judah</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh20:1-Josh20:7\">JOS 20:1–20:7</a> <em>cities of refuge in Judah</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:1-Josh21:4\">JOS 21:1–21:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:9-Josh21:16\">JOS 21:9–21:16</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:1\">1SA 17:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:3-1Sam22:5\">1SA 22:3–22:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam23:21-1Sam23:23\">1SA 23:21–23:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam27:8-1Sam27:10\">1SA 27:8–27:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam30:11-1Sam30:16\">1SA 30:11–30:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam2:1\">2SA 2:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:5-2Sam24:7\">2SA 24:5–24:7</a></p>\n<h3>Early evidence of the distinction between Judah and the other tribes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:9\">2SA 24:9</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr21:5\">1CH 21:5</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:8\">1SA 11:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam17:52\">1SA 17:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:162\">1SA 18:162</a>SA <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:8-1Sam2:11\">2:8–2:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:9-2Sam3:10\">2SA 3:9–3:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam5:5\">2SA 5:5</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:11\">2SA 11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam12:8\">2SA 12:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:40-2Sam20:2\">2SA 19:40–20:2</a> <em>Judah remained loyal to David when Israel rebelled</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam21:2\">2SA 21:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:11\">2SA 24:11</a>KI <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:35\">1:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:20\">1KI 4:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:25\">1KI 4:25</a></p>\n<h3>The separation of Judah from the northern tribes</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:1-1Kgs12:24\">1KI 12:1–12:24</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr10:1-2Chr11:4\">2CH 10:1–11:4</a></p>\n<h3>The continuing tribal identity of Judah</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr19:8-2Chr19:11\">2CH 19:8–19:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:18-2Kgs17:20\">2KI 17:18–17:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:67-Ps78:68\">PSA 78:67–78:68</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek37:15-Ezek37:28\">EZK 37:15–37:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek48:1-Ezek48:8\">EZK 48:1–48:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek48:30-Ezek48:31\">EZK 48:30–48:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:1-Rev7:8\">REV 7:1–7:8</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Levi</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Levi</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:16-Exod6:25\">EXO 6:16–6:25</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:17-Num3:20\">NUM 3:17–3:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:57-Num26:62\">NUM 26:57–26:62</a></p>\n<h3>The tribe of Levi is set apart to God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:25-Exod32:29\">EXO 32:25–32:29</a> <em>Their loyalty to the LORD set them apart.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:47-Num1:53\">NUM 1:47–1:53</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:38\">NUM 3:38</a></p>\n<h3>They were claimed by God as a substitute for the firstborn males of Israel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:11-Num3:13\">NUM 3:11–3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num3:40-Num3:45\">NUM 3:40–3:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num8:15-Num8:18\">NUM 8:15–8:18</a></p>\n<h3>The tribe of Levi received no allotment of land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:1-Deut18:2\">DEU 18:1–18:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:23\">NUM 18:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:32-Josh13:33\">JOS 13:32–13:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:3-Josh14:4\">JOS 14:3–14:4</a></p>\n<h3>The tribe of Levi lived in designated towns</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:1-Num35:8\">NUM 35:1–35:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:32-Lev25:34\">LEV 25:32–25:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:1-Josh21:42\">JOS 21:1–21:42</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:54-1Chr6:80\">1CH 6:54–6:80</a></p>\n<h3>Tithes and offerings given by the rest of Israel supported the tribe of Levi</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num18:21-Num18:24\">NUM 18:21–18:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut14:22-Deut14:29\">DEU 14:22–14:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh10:37-Neh10:38\">NEH 10:37–10:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh13:4-Neh13:13\">NEH 13:4–13:13</a></p>\n<h3>Moses blesses the tribe of Levi</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut33:8-Deut33:11\">DEU 33:8–33:11</a></p>\n<h3>The tribe of Levi in the period of the monarchy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:26-1Chr12:28\">1CH 12:26–12:28</a> <em>Their fighting men join David at Hebron</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr23:2-1Chr23:24\">1CH 23:2–23:24</a> <em>David divides them into three groups and organises their responsibilities</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:16-1Chr27:17\">1CH 27:16–27:17</a> <em>David sets an army officer over them.</em></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Manasseh</h2>\n<h3>The tribe of Manasseh was descended from Joseph's older son</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:4\">JOS 14:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:3-Gen48:20\">GEN 48:3–48:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:28-Num26:37\">NUM 26:28–26:37</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr7:14-1Chr7:19\">1CH 7:14–7:19</a></p>\n<h3>Manasseh in the wilderness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:34-Num1:35\">NUM 1:34–1:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:18-Num2:21\">NUM 2:18–2:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:1-Num27:11\">NUM 27:1–27:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:1-Num36:12\">NUM 36:1–36:12</a></p>\n<h3>The division of Manasseh into two</h3>\n<p>The half-tribe of Manasseh was allocated territory in Gilead:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:33\">NUM 32:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:39-Num32:42\">NUM 32:39–32:42</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:13-Deut3:15\">DEU 3:13–3:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:7-Deut29:8\">DEU 29:7–29:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh12:4-Josh12:6\">JOS 12:4–12:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:29-Josh13:31\">JOS 13:29–13:31</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:23\">1CH 5:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:6-Josh13:7\">JOS 13:6–13:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh16:1-Josh16:4\">JOS 16:1–16:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh17:1-Josh17:13\">JOS 17:1–17:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:27\">JDG 1:27</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:1-Josh22:34\">JOS 22:1–22:34</a> <em>the threat of war against the half-tribe of Manasseh and the other Transjordan tribes</em></p>\n<h3>Manasseh in the period of the judges</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:23\">JDG 7:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:11-Judg6:16\">JDG 6:11–6:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:33-Judg6:35\">JDG 6:33–6:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:1-Judg11:11\">JDG 11:1–11:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg12:1-Judg12:7\">JDG 12:1–12:7</a></p>\n<h3>Manasseh under the monarchy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:26\">1CH 5:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:19-1Chr12:20\">1CH 12:19–12:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:32\">1CH 26:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:9\">2CH 15:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:1-2Chr30:20\">2CH 30:1–30:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:8-2Chr34:9\">2CH 34:8–34:9</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Naphtali</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Naphtali</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:24\">GEN 46:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:48-Num26:50\">NUM 26:48–26:50</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Naphtali</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:42-Num1:43\">NUM 1:42–1:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:25-Num2:30\">NUM 2:25–2:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:12-Deut27:13\">DEU 27:12–27:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:33\">JDG 1:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:4-Judg4:10\">JDG 4:4–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:33-Judg6:35\">JDG 6:33–6:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs15:29\">2KI 15:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:38-1Chr12:40\">1CH 12:38–12:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:1-2Chr34:7\">2CH 34:1–34:7</a></p>\n<h3>The territory of Naphtali</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:1\">ISA 9:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:32-Josh19:39\">JOS 19:32–19:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:13-Matt4:16\">MAT 4:13–4:16</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Reuben</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Reuben</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:5-Num26:7\">NUM 26:5–26:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:8-Gen46:9\">GEN 46:8–46:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:14\">EXO 6:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:1-1Chr5:10\">1CH 5:1–5:10</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Reuben</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:20-Num1:21\">NUM 1:20–1:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:10-Num2:16\">NUM 2:10–2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num16:1-Num16:3\">NUM 16:1–16:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:1-Num32:38\">NUM 32:1–32:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:12-Deut3:17\">DEU 3:12–3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:7-Deut29:8\">DEU 29:7–29:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh13:15-Josh13:23\">JOS 13:15–13:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:12-Josh1:18\">JOS 1:12–1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh4:10-Josh4:13\">JOS 4:10–4:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh22:1-Josh22:34\">JOS 22:1–22:34</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:18-1Chr5:22\">1CH 5:18–5:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr5:25-1Chr5:26\">1CH 5:25–5:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr11:42\">1CH 11:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:37\">1CH 12:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr26:32\">1CH 26:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr27:16\">1CH 27:16</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Simeon</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Simeon</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:15\">EXO 6:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:10\">GEN 46:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:12-Num26:14\">NUM 26:12–26:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr4:24-1Chr4:37\">1CH 4:24–4:37</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Simeon</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:22-Num1:23\">NUM 1:22–1:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:10-Num2:16\">NUM 2:10–2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:1-Josh19:9\">JOS 19:1–19:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr4:38-1Chr4:43\">1CH 4:38–4:43</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:23-1Chr12:25\">1CH 12:23–12:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr15:9\">2CH 15:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:1-2Chr34:7\">2CH 34:1–34:7</a></p>\n<h2>The tribe of Zebulun</h2>\n<h3>The genealogy of Zebulun</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen46:14\">GEN 46:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num26:26-Num26:27\">NUM 26:26–26:27</a></p>\n<h3>The history of Zebulun</h3>\n<p>In the wilderness:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num1:30-Num1:31\">NUM 1:30–1:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num2:3-Num2:9\">NUM 2:3–2:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:12-Deut27:13\">DEU 27:12–27:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:30\">JDG 1:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:6\">JDG 4:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:9-Judg4:10\">JDG 4:9–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:13-Judg5:14\">JDG 5:13–5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg5:18\">JDG 5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:33-Judg6:35\">JDG 6:33–6:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg12:11-Judg12:12\">JDG 12:11–12:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:33\">1CH 12:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr12:40\">1CH 12:40</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr30:10-2Chr30:20\">2CH 30:10–30:20</a></p>\n<h3>The territory of Zebulun</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:1\">ISA 9:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh19:10-Josh19:16\">JOS 19:10–19:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:12-Matt4:16\">MAT 4:12–4:16</a></p>",
